, {"kind": "text", "text": "("}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "yatafar~aEu", "text_ar": "يَتَفَرَّعُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ")"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "from the lower,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "lowest, part"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "thereof: (Msb:) pl."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "furuwEN", "text_ar": "فُرُوعٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "only. (TA.) It is said in a trad."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aY~u Al$~ajari A^aboEadu mina AlxaArifi qaAluwA faroEuhaA", "text_ar": "اَىُّ الشَّجَرِ اَبْعَدُ مِنَ الخَارِفِ قَالُوا فَرْعُهَا"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qaAla waka*`lika AlS~af~u AlA^aw~alu", "text_ar": "قَالَ وَكَذٰلِكَ الصَّفُّ الاَوَّلُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "What part of trees is furthest from the plucker of the fruit? they said, The uppermost part thereof; he said, And such like is the first row"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "of the persons worshipping in the mosque]. (TA.) Thus"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "faroEu AlA^u*uni", "text_ar": "فَرْعُ الاُذُنِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "signifies"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The upper,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "uppermost, part of the ear;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K, * MF, TA;) pl. as above. (TA.) And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "furuwEu", "text_ar": "فُرُوعُ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Almuqolatayoni", "text_ar": "المُقْلَتَيْنِ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The upper,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "uppermost, parts of the two eyeballs."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA.) ―         -b2-  [Hence,]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A branch of a tree"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "plant:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(KL, TA:) or the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "head of a branch:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a great branch:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a branch of anything."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(MA.) ―         -b3-  [And hence, (assumed tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A branch,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "subdivision,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "derivative,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "of anything that is regarded as a fundamental or a whole;]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a thing that is built,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "founded, upon another thing;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "opposed to"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aSolN", "text_ar": "اَصْلٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (K, TA:) [the pl."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "furuwEN", "text_ar": "فُرُوعٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", as opposed to"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^uSuwlN", "text_ar": "اُصُولٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "meaning “ fundamentals, ” signifies, in the conventional language of the lawyers and the men of science in general, the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "derivative institutes of the law,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "&c.: see 2:]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Eilomu", "text_ar": "عِلْمُ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlfuruwEi", "text_ar": "الفُرُوعِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the science of the derivative institutes of the law"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] is what is commonly known by the appellation of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Eilomu Alfiqohi", "text_ar": "عِلْمُ الفِقْهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the science of jurisprudence;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "because it is mainly concerned with institutes derived from fundamentals]. (Hájjee Khaleefeh.) ―         -b4-  And (tropical:)  The"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "hair"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "of a woman: pl. as above [app. used in a collective sense like the French 