text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "between the two acclivities of two mountains"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: (TA:) [but] in this sense its pl. is"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "firaAEN", "text_ar": "فِرَاعٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (K, TA.)       -A2-  Also [or"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qawosN faroEN", "text_ar": "قَوْسٌ فَرْعٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A bow that is made from the extreme portion of a branch,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(As, S, O, K, TA,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "from the head thereof:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(As, TA:) and (K)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a bow that is not"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "made from a branch"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "divided lengthwise"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, O, K, TA) is called"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qawosN", "text_ar": "قَوْسٌ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "faroEN", "text_ar": "فَرْعٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; (S, O, TA;) such as is [made from a branch] divided lengthwise being called"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qawosN", "text_ar": "قَوْسٌ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "filoqN", "text_ar": "فِلْقٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (S, O:) or the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "faroE", "text_ar": "فَرْع"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "one"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of the best of bows:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(AHn, K, TA:) and [this word is used as an epithet, i. e.] one says"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qawosN faroEN", "text_ar": "قَوْسٌ فَرْعٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "faroEapN", "text_ar": "فَرْعَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (K.)       -A3-  Also, i. e."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "faroEN", "text_ar": "فَرْعٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ","}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Property that is beneficial,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "serviceable, and made ready,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "prepared:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(O, K, TA:) or, accord. to the S, it is ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "faraEN", "text_ar": "فَرَعٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "which has this signification; but this is said by Sgh [app. in the TS], and after him by the author of the K, to be a mistake; and a verse in which it occurs with the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "r", "text_ar": "ر"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "quiescent is cited in the O and K as an ex. of it in this sense: it may be, however, that the poet has made the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "r", "text_ar": "ر"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "quiescent of necessity [by poetic license, for the sake of the metre]; or it may here [properly] signify “ a branch, ” and be metonymically used as meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "recent property."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA.)       -A4-  See also the next paragraph, latter half."}], "source_refs": ["Msb", "KL", "TA", "K", "S", "O", "As", "AHn"]}]}, "classical_definitions": null, "translations_attribution": {"model": "qwen36-35b-heretic", "generated_date": "2026-05-18", "pipeline_version": "words.translation.v1.spark"}}